# Doudou — extra sdkconfig defaults for Wokwi preview.
#
# Use:
#   idf.py -DSDKCONFIG_DEFAULTS="sdkconfig.defaults;sdkconfig.defaults.wokwi" reconfigure
#   idf.py build
#   then run the Wokwi simulator (diagram.json).
#
# What it does:
#   * Flips DOUDOU_LCD_INVERT_COLOR + DOUDOU_LCD_BGR_ORDER off so the
#     ILI9341 model in Wokwi (used as a stand-in for GC9A01) shows the
#     intended colours instead of an inverted BGR negative.
#
# What it does NOT fix:
#   * Wokwi's ILI9341 is 240×320 rectangular; firmware paints only the
#     top 240×240. The bottom 80 lines show uninitialised LCD content.
#     Mentally crop to the top square — the visible UI is correct.
#   * Wi-Fi is a gateway mock and won't reach a real Bridge.
#   * BLE is not modelled at all — this build still uses the default
#     WS transport (set in sdkconfig.defaults).

CONFIG_DOUDOU_LCD_FOR_WOKWI=y
